@NODE Introduction "Introduction"
@TOC Main
@{LINDENT 1}

@{b}Introduction@{ub}



Tabulator is program that will scan a C source code file and adjust all
the tabs to your specified value.  It will also adjust any "improper" code.
Comments may also be removed if desired.


Since no 2 programmers write code in the same manner, this program is
needed if you wish to easily port others persons code.  If they use a tab of 8
spaces and you only use 4, it can be a major pain to manually reset each line's
tab settings, not to mention very time consuming and mind numbing.  Tabulator
makes easy work of this job for you.


Any code you adjust is assumed to be correct in the sense that each open
bracket, '{', has a matching close bracket, '}', that each line command is
terminated correctly, all comments are set correctly, etc.


Multiple files may be processed so entire programming projects can easily
be adjusted with minimal effort.



Example:


    do {

        Get;

        Print;

    } while(!Terminated);


    for(x=1; x<100; x++)

    Printf(x);


    for(x=1; x<100; x++)

    {

        Printf(x);

        Printf(y);

    }


    if (a==1) b=2;

    else b=3;


    if (x==2)

        y=3;

    else

        y=4;


    if (x==4)

    {

        z=4;

        a=2;

    }

    else

    {

        z=5;

        a=3;

    }


    if (x==4) y=0;

    else if (x==5) y=1;

    else y=2;



Tabulator Output:


