@NODE StartingProg "Starting Tabulator"
@TOC UsingProgram
@{LINDENT 1}

@{b}Starting Tabulator@{ub}



This program may be started from the Workbench or the Shell window.


This program will detach from the Shell so you need not use Run or any
other variant.  There are a few command line arguments you may use when loading:



@{b}FILE/K@{ub}

C source code file to process.  You specify wildcards in the path.

ex: Tabulator FILE #?.c


@{b}TABSIZE/K@{ub}

Set the tab size.  0-16

Will override the saved preferences.


@{b}EXTENSION/K@{ub}

Extension to append to newly created source file.

default: .tab
Will override the saved preferences.


@{b}REMOVECOMMENTS/K@{ub}

Toggle removal of all comments.

REMOVECOMMENTS=TRUE or REMOVECOMMENTS=FALSE.

Will override the saved preferences.


@{b}ICONIFY/S@{ub}

Start in iconified mode.


@{b}ICON_X/K@{ub}

X coordinate for AppIcon.


@{b}ICON_Y/K@{ub}

Y coordinate for AppIcon.


@{b}NOVERSION/S@{ub}

Do not display program title when not using the editor.


@{b}UI/K@{ub}

Open or keep the user interface closed.

UI=TRUE or UI=FALSE.


@{b}PUBSCREEN/K@{ub}

Name of public screen to open the interface on.


@{b}LANGUAGE/K@{ub}

Preferred locale strings language.

Language must be all lower case.


@{b}DONOTDETACH/S@{ub}

Do not detach from the Shell.



The arguments are not case sensitive and may be mixed in any order.

ex: Tabulator FILE Main.c REMOVECOMMENTS TABSIZE 4


