@NODE OperationNotes "Operation Notes"
@TOC Main
@{LINDENT 1}

@{b}Operation Notes@{ub}



Press the Help key for AmigaGuide help.


It can be started in WBStartup and iconified so it is always available.


Tabulator assumes that any source it processes is already correct, or it
could cause the output to be totally incorrect.


If using Remove Comments, the first comment of the file will not be
removed.  This is to allow for a header message.


@{b}Every CASE must have a matching BREAK; for proper operation!@{ub}


    switch(EasyRequest(...))

    {

        case 1: goto Top;

        case 2: goto Middle;

        case 0: goto Bottom;

    }


The above will not work properly.


    switch(EasyRequest(...))

    {

        case 1: goto Top;

                break;


        case 2: goto Middle;

                break;


        case 0: goto Bottom;

                break;

    }


The above will.


