@NODE Incompatibilities "Incompatibilities"
@TOC Main
@{LINDENT 1}

@{b}Incompatibilities@{ub}



As of this version, Tabulator will make all switch()/case calls in this
manner:


    switch(Gadget)

    {

        case MAIN_OK:

            Printf("OK");

            break;


        case MAIN_QUIT:

            Printf("Quit");

            break;


        default:

            break;

    }


Hopefully a future revision will allow for:


    case MAIN_OK:       Printf("OK");

                        break;


    case MAIN_QUIT:     Printf("Quit");

                        break;


    default:            break;


This is my preferred style, so I will be working on it.


@ENDNODE


